==English==
===Etymology===
The term contact juggling was coined by James Ernest in a book of the same name.

===Noun===
'''[[contact]] [[juggling]]'''
{{wikipedia}}
#the art of moving a single ball or mutiple balls, as by [[rolling]] or [[spinning]].  The defining characteristic of contact juggling is that the artist stays in Contact with the ball or balls rather than throwing them. 

